  <p> I was born in Spain, but I have lived in Croatia, Taiwan, India,
Panama and United States.
    Now, I enjoy the awesome weather of Nairobi (Kenya).
    </p>

  <h2 style="text-align:center"><br><i class="fa fa-graduation-cap"></i> & <i class="fa fa-keyboard-o"></i></h2>
  <p style="text-align:center"><img src="/assets/mba-web-teleco.png">
  </p>

  <p>I hold an MBA degree from the <a href="http://www.isb.edu">Indian School of Business</a> thanks to a full grant of
    <a href="https://fundacionlacaixa.org/"> Fundación "laCaixa"</a>. I am a telecommunications engineer and I have a postgraduate on web technologies.
  </p>
  <p>Currently, I am proudly working for the United Nations pushing the
<a hreg="https://digitalpublicgoods.net/ title="Digital Public Goods
Alliance website">Digital Public Goods</a> within
UNICEF's Digital Centre of Excellence in Nairobi (Kenya). Earlier, in this
organization, I was designing and leading the 
    development of internal global enterprise applications.
    In the past, I created from scratch and lead the user
    experience team of the foremost bank of Panama,
    <a href="http://www.bancogeneral.com" title="Banco General website">Banco General</a>, I founded
    a <a href="http://www.adianteapps.com" title="Open Adiante Apps
website">startup company</a>,
    I worked as mobile app project
    manager for <a href="http://www.bbva.com" title="Banco Bilbao
Vizcaya Argentaria">BBVA</a>, and I was part of
    the <acronym title="User Experience">UX</acronym> team of one of the largest mobile operators in the world,
    <a href="http://www.telefonica.com" title="Telefonica's website">Telefónica Movistar</a>.
    <br>
